OL,3,CCould Alderney change Guernsey
OL,4,Crelationship and strengthen Jersey
OL,5,Cties?
OL,7,FGuernsey States Member, Deputy Peter
OL,8,FRoffey, believes this arrangement
OL,9,Fshould now be revisited, saying: "I
OL,10,Fthink any agreement that's coming up
OL,11,Fto 80-years-old obviously needs
OL,12,Freviewing. We're living in a different
OL,13,Fworld to the immediate post-war
OL,14,Fenvironment when it was signed."
OL,16,FHe adds: "What I would not want to do,
OL,17,Funlike a few colleagues, is
OL,18,Ffundamentally change the assumption
OL,19,Fthat we work together on a cooperative
OL,20,Fbasis.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G2/9
